    <body>
        <p><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Affects Appearance </span>If selected, this style defines the appearance of the text (font, color, etc.) in the target Help file. If cleared, the style is only used to create a hotspot or keyword and does not affect target appearance. Character styles with this check box selected can be used to specify the appearance of links generated by other means. For example, a style with Affect Appearance selected and a Type = None can be used to format topic links, dynamic links, and margin notes if you need to override the default link appearance for them. </p>
